message: On second thought, forget all of this. I'm being a bit too overzealous with my opinion, and I have no particular reason to step on toes either way.

My page on VG character Ashley Robbins is being questioned for notability for having her own page despite her being a prominent aspect of point-and-click game culture, and citing her involvement in scholar studies. A page for an obscure Ace Attorney supporting character over being memed on a little doesn't cut the mustard, I'm sorry. I'm not gonna just remove the page, since I'm not an authority, but I'm just using common sense here.
I don't need your threats, thanks
WP:IDONTLIKEIT is not valid. No one has taken this to the talk page.
Again, this is based on WP:IDONTLIKEIT and subjective interpretation. Take this to the talk page, or some other venue, at least.
Message from a user trying to threaten me over subjective bias

The sourcing is there. Your argument here is based on WP:IDONTLIKEIT because a  subjective interpretation of the sources. Leaving a message on my talk page also doesn't help make your subjective IDONTLIKIT argument any less ridiculous.
